00:37:45.820 --> 00:37:48.780
This is an interesting tool.

00:37:48.940 --> 00:37:49.900
Yes, sure.

00:37:50.020 --> 00:37:52.500
Sometimes we fire it up
and use it for different things.

00:37:53.300 --> 00:38:00.420
We've had some inconsistencies
in what has been reported,

00:38:00.620 --> 00:38:03.460
and that is why
we use more than one tool.

00:38:03.980 --> 00:38:08.020
We've had some false contrast checks

00:38:08.180 --> 00:38:11.620
that have actually been picked up
by our developers.

00:38:11.740 --> 00:38:15.180
That's not quite right
and then done a manual check.

00:38:15.380 --> 00:38:19.260
Whilst we do use this for some things,

00:38:19.380 --> 00:38:23.540
we don't really use it
for accessibility testing so much

00:38:23.740 --> 00:38:26.420
as we did maybe 12,
18 months ago.

00:38:28.220 --> 00:38:29.860
When using these tools,

00:38:30.300 --> 00:38:33.260
it's essential to remember
that automated testing

00:38:33.380 --> 00:38:39.060
is not a replacement
for expertise and manual testing.

00:38:40.140 --> 00:38:42.780
We need to visually
and technically assess

00:38:43.380 --> 00:38:46.900
and use our judgment to identify any issues

00:38:47.020 --> 00:38:49.940
that may not be caught
by automated tools.

00:38:50.740 --> 00:38:52.420
Just one tip here.

00:38:52.940 --> 00:38:55.180
When using automated testing tools,

00:38:55.380 --> 00:39:00.460
be mindful of false positives
and negatives or even miss things.

00:39:00.660 --> 00:39:04.820
Don't take the output
of any automated testing tool as gospel.

00:39:05.660 --> 00:39:08.700
That's why I say we use
a couple of different ones,

00:39:08.780 --> 00:39:12.820
maybe three at times,
and we use our own expertise

00:39:13.020 --> 00:39:17.140
and manual interpretation
to validate those results.

00:39:20.900 --> 00:39:23.540
As we've explored
throughout this presentation,

00:39:23.660 --> 00:39:27.540
accessibility
is not just a moral imperative,

00:39:27.900 --> 00:39:33.500
but a critical component of creating inclusive
and usable digital products.

00:39:34.420 --> 00:39:38.060
We've seen how integrating
accessibility into every stage

00:39:38.220 --> 00:39:41.020
of the development process
and sales process,

00:39:41.140 --> 00:39:44.100
even before that,
from design to testing,

00:39:44.260 --> 00:39:48.180
can ensure that our digital products
are accessible to all users,

00:39:48.380 --> 00:39:53.180
regardless of their abilities,
whilst maintaining commercial viability.

00:39:53.940 --> 00:39:58.380
We've also addressed the common concern
that accessibility costs more.

00:39:59.620 --> 00:40:00.860
As we've demonstrated here,

00:40:01.300 --> 00:40:04.340
considering accessibility
from start to finish

00:40:04.460 --> 00:40:10.180
can actually save costs in the long run
by avoiding costly retrofits

00:40:10.300 --> 00:40:13.620
or a big push at the end
when you suddenly realize,

00:40:13.780 --> 00:40:15.420
"Oh, I've left it to the last minute."

00:40:15.620 --> 00:40:16.700
Please don't do that.

00:40:16.940 --> 00:40:19.500
We want to ensure
that our digital products

00:40:19.620 --> 00:40:22.700
are usable
by the widest audience we can.

00:40:23.740 --> 00:40:26.940
With a skilled team, high accessibility

00:40:27.060 --> 00:40:30.220
can be partnered
with creative, innovative design.

00:40:30.740 --> 00:40:32.380
I can assure you of that.

00:40:32.540 --> 00:40:36.100
We've seen how semantic structure,
color contrast,

00:40:36.220 --> 00:40:41.940
and clean content can enhance
the user experience for all users,

00:40:42.340 --> 00:40:45.180
whilst also ensuring
that our digital products

00:40:45.300 --> 00:40:49.660
are accessible to those users
that have disabilities.

00:40:51.300 --> 00:40:54.460
As I start to wind up this presentation now,

00:40:54.620 --> 00:40:57.140
I want to leave you
with a key takeaway.

00:40:57.980 --> 00:41:05.220
Accessibility is not a trade off
between creativity and inclusivity.

00:41:05.740 --> 00:41:11.340
Rather, it's a fundamental aspect
of creating digital products

00:41:11.500 --> 00:41:17.860
that are usable, accessible,
and inclusive for all users.

00:41:18.740 --> 00:41:22.940
By prioritizing accessibility
and incorporating it

00:41:23.060 --> 00:41:27.140
into every stage of our development process
from start to finish,

00:41:27.620 --> 00:41:30.140
we can create products and websites

00:41:30.300 --> 00:41:32.900
that are not only compliant
with regulations,

00:41:33.340 --> 00:41:39.620
but ultimately, as I said,
provide a better user experience for all users.

00:41:39.740 --> 00:41:44.580
Let's make accessibility
a core part of our design

00:41:44.740 --> 00:41:46.020
and development process

00:41:46.180 --> 00:41:50.340
and create a more inclusive
digital landscape for everyone.

