00:48:59.660 --> 00:49:03.580
I can share a couple
of insights around that part at least.

00:49:04.020 --> 00:49:14.260
Recruiting for user testing can be costly,
complicated, very time consuming.

00:49:14.420 --> 00:49:17.820
The more narrower you get
on the demographic

00:49:17.940 --> 00:49:20.500
of the type of person
that you want to participate,

00:49:20.660 --> 00:49:24.580
the narrower it gets,
the harder it gets.

00:49:27.540 --> 00:49:32.740
There are various websites
that help you recruit users,

00:49:32.900 --> 00:49:37.340
user interviews,
user testing.com.

00:49:37.540 --> 00:49:40.020
All these have a price tag to them.

00:49:40.180 --> 00:49:44.980
They have a pool of users and you can set up
screener questions and things like that.

00:49:46.180 --> 00:49:50.540
As I say, the narrower you get
on the criteria for recruitment,

00:49:50.660 --> 00:49:51.820
the harder it gets.

00:49:52.020 --> 00:49:55.300
Frankly, you may actually
need to go down

00:49:55.380 --> 00:49:59.260
a more specialized bespoke recruitment route

00:49:59.460 --> 00:50:03.660
to find suitable testers
with disabilities.

00:50:03.820 --> 00:50:11.980
Also, don't discount going
into communities, forums,

00:50:12.100 --> 00:50:13.860
LinkedIn groups, support groups,

00:50:14.020 --> 00:50:16.540
things like that
and asking the honest question.

00:50:16.700 --> 00:50:19.540
What I will leave you
with is a final nugget.

00:50:19.700 --> 00:50:24.900
If you want people to participate
and engage with user testing,

00:50:25.460 --> 00:50:27.460
please don't expect it for free.

00:50:28.020 --> 00:50:31.020
Any user testers should be rewarded.

00:50:31.180 --> 00:50:35.540
You will find if you try to hop-skip that
and not reward them,

00:50:37.140 --> 00:50:38.140
people won't turn up.

00:50:38.300 --> 00:50:39.940
They won't be engaged.

00:50:40.100 --> 00:50:42.260
Hell, they probably won't even apply.

00:50:42.420 --> 00:50:46.140
As a rough guide,
you're probably looking

00:50:46.300 --> 00:50:50.220
at the user testing session
shouldn't be more than half an hour.

00:50:50.420 --> 00:50:51.860
They should be half an hour or less.

00:50:52.020 --> 00:50:55.300
You're probably looking
at a rough range

00:50:55.460 --> 00:51:00.300
depending on the type of person
and lots of different factors of around--

